sec.p:
In order to assess the univariate association between diarrhea caused by rotavirus and number of children vaccinated with Rota 2, Pearson Correlation coefficient is computed between monthly diarrhea cases and Rota 2 as well as lagged values of Rota 2 and diarrhea cases. The lagged values are considered to know which previous month’s Rota 2 is strongly associated with diarrhea cases in the district and which lagged values of Diarrhea provides information about its future values. Diarrhea at time t is denoted by (yt) and Rota by (xt). Thus previous k months Diarrhea and Rota2 will thus be (yt − k) and (xt − k) respectively. Pearson correlation between any two variables (xi, yi). is given by
