				\begin{document}$$ F=\frac{SSB}{k-1}\div \frac{SSW}{n-k} $$\end{document}F=SSBk−1÷SSWn−k

Commonly, it is stated as ARIMA (p,d,q), where p is the number of lags of the response variable (yt) used as regressors, d is the number of times (yt) is differenced to make it stationary, and q is the errors associated with forecasting the series (yt). The full ARIMA model when the data are stationary is given by:
